Z = extension(A, A + dir(a), B, B + dir(a + 45));

draw(X--Z--Y--C--A);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, N);
label("$C$", C, E);
label("$X$", X, SE);
label("$Y$", Y, S);
label("$Z$", Z, NW);
label("$11$", (A + B)/2, S);
label("$7$", (B + C)/2, N);
label("$\alpha$", A, NE);
[/asy]

Therefore, the maximum area of triangle $XYZ$ is $\boxed{85}.$

