draw(G--C);
label("$A$",A,W);
label("$B$",B,E);
label("$C$",C,E);
label("$D$",D,S);
label("$E$",G,W);
[/asy]
Also $CD=DE=EC$, so $\triangle CDE$ is equilateral and $\angle CED =
60^\circ$.  Therefore \[
